By Lizzy Okoji Governor Yahaya Bello of Kogi State has sends felicitation to President Muhammadu Buhari, First Lady, Aisha Buhari, Muslim faithfuls and all Nigerians on the celebration of Eid-Il- Fitri. Yahaya Bello who is also Chairman, Youth, Women and Persons with Disabilities Committee for the APC Membership Registration and Revalidation made this known in a video message made available to the News Agency of Nigeria on Friday. The governor in his message called on Nigerians to continue to pray for the peace and harmony of the country at this time and beyond as he taxed Nigerians on peaceful coexistence and National Orientation.  The governor in the message also felicitated with Senate President Ahmed Lawan, Speaker of the House of Representatives, Femi Gbajabiamila and all Members of the National Assembly. In his message, Bello also greeted governor Mai Mala Buni, of Yobe who is also the Care taker Chairman of the APC, Alhaji Sa’adu Abubakar, Sultan of Sokoto, Alhaji Ado Ibrahim, Ohinoyi of Ebiraland, and all traditional rulers across the country. (NAN) Share this:WhatsAppFacebookTwitterTelegramMoreLinkedInTumblrSkypeRedditPinterestPocket Share this:WhatsAppFacebookTwitterTelegramMoreLinkedInTumblrSkypeRedditPinterestPocket WhatsAppFacebookTwitterTelegramMoreLinkedInTumblrSkypeRedditPinterestPocket LinkedInTumblrSkypeRedditPinterestPocket LinkedInTumblrSkypeRedditPinterestPocket Like this:Like Loading... Like Loading...  	Related Crisis Management: Governors pay `Thank You’ visit to BuhariBy Ismaila Chafe President Muhammadu Buhari on Friday received the Progressive Governors’ Forum led by Gov. Atiku Bagudu, who paid him 'thank you' visit. The governors thanked President Buhari for his efforts toward resolving the crisis facing the All Progressives Congress (APC). Speaking to State House correspondents at the end…June 26, 2020In "Politics"Arewa Youths call on Yahaya Bello to run for President in 2023Arewa Youth Forum (AYF) calls on Gov. Yahaya Bello of Kogi to r